formats.method_only: create launch template. Creates a launch template. A launch template contains the parameters to launch an instance. When you launch an instance using Run Instances, you can specify a launch template instead of providing the launch parameters in the request. For more information, see Store instance launch parameters in Amazon EC2 launch templates in the Amazon EC2 User Guide. To clone an existing launch template as the basis for a new launch template, use the Amazon EC2 console. The API, SD Ks, and CLI do not support cloning a template. For more information, see Create a launch template from an existing launch template in the Amazon EC2 User Guide.
formats.with_params: create launch template. Creates a launch template. A launch template contains the parameters to launch an instance. To clone an existing launch template as the basis for a new launch template, use the Amazon EC2 console. The API, SD Ks, and CLI do not support cloning a template. For more information, see Create a launch template from an existing launch template in the Amazon EC2 User Guide. This optimization isn't available with all instance types. Additional usage charges apply when using an EBS-optimized instance. The following are the supported values for each volume type: gp3: 3,000 - 16,000 IOPS io1: 100 - 64,000 IOPS io2: 100 - 256,000 IOPS For io2 volumes, you can achieve up to 256,000 IOPS on instances built on the Nitro System. When you launch an instance using Run Instances, you can specify a launch template instead of providing the launch parameters in the request. For more information, see Store instance launch parameters in Amazon EC2 launch templates in the Amazon EC2 User Guide. To clone an existing launch template as the basis for a new launch template, use the Amazon EC2 console. The API, SD Ks, and CLI do not support cloning a template. For more information, see Create a launch template from an existing launch template in the Amazon EC2 User Guide. This field is autopopulated if not provided. | Launch Template Name: A name for the launch template. | Version Description | Launch Template Data: The information for the launch template. The tags to apply to a resource when the resource is being created. When you specify a tag, you must specify the resource type to tag, otherwise the request will fail. Resource Type The type of resource to tag on creation. Tags The tags to apply to the resource. Describes a tag. Key The key of the tag. Constraints: Tag keys are case-sensitive and accept a maximum of 127 Unicode characters. May not begin with aws:. Value The value of the tag. Constraints: Tag values are case-sensitive and accept a maximum of 256 Unicode characters. Returns: Launch Template: Information about the launch template.
